id: pm-bqg4
title: Strengthen SDK typing for extension registration contracts
description: "SDK/extension audit found extension-facing registration types that are too loose (Record<string, unknown> style payloads), which weakens autocomplete and compile-time validation for schema/search/service extension authors and increases trial-and-error integration."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 1
tags[6]: agent-ux,extensions,external-audit,pm-cli,sdk,types
created_at: "2026-04-26T09:56:34.292Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-26T13:16:31.724Z"
assignee: codex-agent
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 180
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exports concrete extension registration interfaces for schema/search/service payloads, examples compile with those types, and extension authoring docs reflect the typed contracts."
parent: pm-o7be
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-o7be,parent,"2026-04-26T09:56:34.292Z",codex-agent,null
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T09:56:34.292Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'Extension SDK schema type definitions Record unknown' --limit 10; pm search 'SchemaFieldDefinition Record unknown ExtensionApi typing' --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Net-new because existing open SDK issue pm-1etl covers module resolution/diagnostics,not compile-time contract precision for extension registration payloads."
  "2026-04-26T09:57:29.339Z",codex-agent,"SDK audit evidence: src/core/extensions/loader.ts currently aliases multiple extension registration contracts as Record<string, unknown> (SchemaFieldDefinition, SchemaItemTypeDefinition, SearchProviderDefinition, VectorStoreAdapterDefinition), which limits compile-time validation and editor guidance for extension authors. Recommend promoting these to explicit interfaces in SDK exports."
  "2026-04-26T13:16:31.724Z",cursor-agent,"Fresh SDK audit evidence 2026-04-26: external-style TypeScript smoke using defineExtension, ExtensionApi, and CommandDefinition compiled successfully after including required manifest priority. pm contracts --flags-only exposed all 52 PM_CORE_COMMAND_NAMES with no missing core commands; remaining DX gap is still the loose Record<string, unknown> aliases for FlagDefinition, SchemaFieldDefinition, SchemaItemTypeDefinition, SchemaMigrationDefinition, SearchProviderDefinition, and VectorStoreAdapterDefinition."
files[2]{path,scope,note}:
  src/core/extensions/loader.ts,project,Extension API registration typing surface audited for loose payload contracts
  src/sdk/index.ts,project,SDK export surface reviewed for extension authoring DX
docs[1]{path,scope,note}:
  docs/EXTENSIONS.md,project,Extension authoring docs to align with stronger SDK type contracts
